This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image classification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also introduces new techniques for improving the robustness of CNNs, which could potentially fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves modifications to the dropout technique, which is a common regularization method in neural networks, and could be relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its techniques on the ImageNet dataset, which is a popular benchmark for image classification, and could be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
